  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nMetrics from https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/3808 show that peers have high P7 penalties dragging the score down a lot. Without evindence yet, it seems that it's caused to broken promises. The peer actually delivers the message but _pubish is not called in time since wait times in queues can be very long.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-02-28 23-41-19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/156044100-65f23c73-e6f8-4aa5-9580-f18f30c5859b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nDon't penalize peers for long queue times\r\n\r\n",
